author: dennisl
msg: [MCHANGELOG-16] when using svn, links are wrong.
o Rearrange the code so that "displayFileDetailUrl" is used if and only if it is supplied in the configuration.

o Add a special token %FILE% that can be put anywhere in "displayFileDetailUrl". The token will be replaced with the actual path to the file when the report is generated. This enables the user to have more complex URLs than was previously possible.

author: jdillon
msg: Install an ArtifactLookup into a thread local to allow the cached G kernel's repo adapter to resolved based on the current project
For some crazy reason some CAR builds depend on themselves... so when the artifact is the same as the project being built
do not resolve and only return the path in the repo where it _should_ exist, else if we return null a bunch of stuff breaks
Cache artifacts once we resolve them to prevent needing to ask mvn to keep resolving them over and over
